  "body": "#### System information\r\n\r\nGeth version: v1.13.1\r\nCL client & version: lighthouse@v4.4.1\r\nOS & Version: Linux\r\nRAM: 40GB\r\nCPU(s): 12\r\n\r\n#### Problem\r\nIn archive node mode (mainnet), RAM leaks and the node process crashes. We detected this problem based on Grafana statistics. Node crashes ones a day. Here are the node launch parameters:\r\n```\r\n [\"geth\", \"--metrics\", \"--metrics.port=6060\", \"--metrics.expensive\", \"--metrics.addr=0.0.0.0\",\r\n\"--authrpc.addr=0.0.0.0\",\"--authrpc.port\",\"8551\", \"--authrpc.vhosts=*\", \"--syncmode\", \"full\",\r\n\"--http\", \"--http.addr\", \"0.0.0.0\", \"--http.port\", \"63115\",\r\n\"--http.api\",\"eth,web3,personal,debug,net,admin\", \r\n\"--ws\", \"--ws.origins=*\", \"--ws.addr=0.0.0.0\", \"--ws.port=63116\", \"--ws.api\", \"eth,web3,personal,debug,net,admin\",\r\n \"--datadir\", \"/data/ethereum\", \"--datadir.minfreedisk\", \"300\",  \"--cache=16384\", \"--snapshot=false\",\r\n\"--port\", \"33332\", \"--gcmode=archive\", \"--maxpeers=100\"]\r\n```\r\n\r\n",
